This paper deals with the weight distribution of random binary linear codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the analysis of random variables and their moments, which falls under the categories of computer science (cs.CC) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the study of codes and their properties is relevant to the field of data structures (cs.DS).
